    <p><strong>BREAKTHROUGH MOMENT</strong></p>

    <p>After a long, courageous journey of self-discovery (and three rounds of VC funding), we at LumaSense™ — the world’s first AI-powered Emotional Orientation Platform for the Blind™ — have finally realised something radical:</p>

    <p>We… don’t actually know any blind people.</p>
    <p>We know. Shocked us too.</p>

    <p>We’ve spent months empowering the narrative, raising awareness, leveraging disability hashtags, and photoshopping white canes into stock photography. We even ran a campaign called #EmpathyEnabled that did really well with lifestyle bloggers.</p>

    <p>But somehow — and we’re still unpacking this — we forgot to talk to an actual blind person.</p>

    <p>Luckily, we’ve got Big Charli™ on retainer, and she’s helping us pivot gracefully into the accountability phase of our product journey.</p>

    <p>That’s why today, we’re opening our hearts, our minds, and our community engagement budget to the very people we heroically built our roadmap around.</p>

    <p>If you are blind, or pretending to be blind for artistic purposes (no, not again, Brenda), we would love to hear your truth and gently funnel it into a compelling brand narrative. You will of course be credited vaguely as “a voice in the community.”</p>

    <p>Because here at LumaSense™, we don’t just build assistive tech. We build awareness platforms with patent-pending compassion loops™.</p>

